BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "22-R-IM-JL-28.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A toy is made of a square with 4 semi-circles of radius [`r = [$r]\ \textrm{cm}`] attached. 
It has a mass of [`m = [$m]\ \textrm{g}`] and a radius of gyration [`k = [$k]\ \textrm{cm}`]
about its center of mass [`G`]. If it rolls to the left without slipping and has [`[$T]\ \textrm{J}`] of
kinetic energy at this moment, find the linear momentum of the toy, the angular momentum
about its center of mass [`G`] and its angular momentum about the point of contact with the ground
[`O`]. The center of mass is directly above the point of contact with the ground.

[`L = `] [____________]{"$L"} [`\hat{i}\ \textrm{kg·m/s}`]

[`H_G = `] [____________]{"$H_G"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]

[`H_O = `] [____________]{"$H_O"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]

END_PGML

